==Demographics==
[[File:Terrebonne, Oregon.JPG|left|thumb|upright|A restaurant in Terrebonne]]
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 1,469 people, 531 households, and 409 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|325.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 561 housing units at an average density of {{convert|124.2|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 94.49% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.07% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.95% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.14% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 2.18% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2.18% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 4.56% of the population.

